---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<Layout title="Contribute to DevDocs" description="Learn how to contribute to the DevDocs documentation site">
  <main class="contribute-page">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[
        { label: 'Contribute', href: '/contribute' }
      ]} />
      
      <h1>Contribute to DevDocs</h1>
      
      <p class="intro">
        We welcome contributions from the community to make DevDocs better for everyone. Whether you're fixing a typo, adding a new article, or improving existing content, your help is appreciated!
      </p>
      
      <section class="how-to">
        <h2>How to Contribute</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <h3>Fork the Repository</h3>
            <p>Start by forking our GitHub repository to your own account.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Set Up Your Development Environment</h3>
            <p>Clone your forked repository and install dependencies:</p>
            <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/yourusername/devdocs.git
cd devdocs
npm install</code></pre>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Create a New Branch</h3>
            <p>Create a new branch for your contribution:</p>
            <pre><code>git checkout -b your-feature-name</code></pre>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Make Your Changes</h3>
            <p>Add or modify content in the <code>src/content/articles</code> directory. Articles are written in Markdown format.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Test Your Changes</h3>
            <p>Run the development server to preview your changes:</p>
            <pre><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Submit a Pull Request</h3>
            <p>When you're satisfied with your changes, commit them, push to your fork, and submit a pull request to our main repository.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>
      
      <section class="guidelines">
        <h2>Article Guidelines</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Frontmatter</strong>: Each article should include frontmatter with title, description, publication date, category, and tags.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Clear Structure</strong>: Use proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3) to organize content.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Code Examples</strong>: Include practical, well-commented code examples that readers can understand and use.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Accessibility</strong>: Ensure your content is accessible to all readers, including proper alt text for images.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Technical Accuracy</strong>: Double-check that all technical information is accurate and up-to-date.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      
      <section class="ideas">
        <h2>Article Ideas</h2>
        <p>Looking for inspiration? Here are some topics we'd love to see covered:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Advanced CSS techniques (animations, layouts, responsive design)</li>
          <li>JavaScript performance optimization</li>
          <li>Building accessible web applications</li>
          <li>API security best practices</li>
          <li>Testing strategies for web applications</li>
          <li>Developer productivity tools and techniques</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      
      <section class="contact">
        <h2>Questions?</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about contributing, feel free to <a href="mailto:contact@devdocs.example.com">email us</a> or open an issue on our GitHub repository.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="https://github.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cta-button">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
